wiki.summary: "Push Ups" is a non-album single released by Toronto rapper Drake. The track is a diss track from Drake responding to various beefs, namely his conflicts with Kendrick Lamar and Metro Boomin that were notably escalated in March-April 2024 through several songs (e.g. “Like That”, “Magic Don Juan (Princess Diana)”, “All To Myself”, “Show of Hands”) across WE DON'T TRUST YOU and WE STILL DON'T TRUST YOU, Metro and Future’s duo of collaborative albums. Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: "Push Ups" is a non-album single released by Toronto rapper Drake. The track is a diss track from Drake responding to various beefs, namely his conflicts with Kendrick Lamar and Metro Boomin that were notably escalated in March-April 2024 through several songs (e.g. “Like That”, “Magic Don Juan (Princess Diana)”, “All To Myself”, “Show of Hands”) across WE DON'T TRUST YOU and WE STILL DON'T TRUST YOU, Metro and Future’s duo of collaborative albums. The track was initially previewed on April 13, 2024. On the same day, a teaser billboard from Spotify teases a new song from Drake that seemingly ties in with the diss track. The track was officially released on streaming on April 19, 2024. The cover art depicts a shoe-size label for a men’s size 7 shoe, notably the size of Kendrick’s shoes, as referenced in the track (How you big-steppin’ with a size 7 men's on?). Read more on Last.fm.
